article.headline: Gardner-Webb 86, High Point 71
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. (AP) -- Grayson Flittner scored 20 points Tuesday night to lead Gardner-Webb past High Point 86-71. Thomas Sanders had 15 points and 10 rebounds for the Runnin' Bulldogs (5-4), who had five players score in double figures. Takayo Siddle added 14 points off the bench as Gardner-Webb shot 59 percent. Arizona Reid had 29 points and nine rebounds to lead the Panthers (2-3). Flittner scored 17 points to help Gardner-Webb build a 46-35 halftime lead, then nailed a 3-pointer to open the second half. High Point got as close as six with about 12 1/2 minutes left before Gardner-Webb responded with a pair of baskets from Siddle. High Point got no closer than nine points the rest of the way and trailed by as many as 18 late. The game was a matchup of future Big South Conference rivals. Gardner-Webb is playing its final season in the Atlantic Sun Conference.
